{"version":1,"ops":[{"author":{"id":"9eb510892d1accc0c715d21128d216b2e6f74967"},"files":null,"message":"The thing with welcome now (other than it's over a decade old) is that it uses\nonly assets from the builtin resources. If those are changed (which is often\nthe case when durden and others are installed), the icon is missing and the\nfont is missing, resulting in a black screen.\n\nTwo changes that would fix this problem is a. to have a fallback bitmap font\nbuiltin, which would come with the tui refactor anyhow and b. to write the appl\nto be less useless, i.e. other visual indicators that can be used for\ndiagnostics.","timestamp":1563722902,"title":"(welcome) make the included appl less useless","type":1}]}